{{Otheruses|Amber}}
'''Amber''' was the name of a [[Bodyguard/Legends|bodyguard]] attached to the royal family of [[Aquilae (The Star Wars)|Aquilae]] when the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] threatened to annex its system. Amber had one arm, and was a [[Landspeeder/Legends|landspeeder]] driver. He drove [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia]] and her [[Handmaiden/Legends|handmaidens]] to [[Yuell]] so she could enroll in the [[Chatos Academy]]. He presumably remained with [[Mina (handmaiden)|Mina]] when she remained at the Academy and impersonated Leia to throw off the Empire. The real Leia and [[Alana]] left with [[Annikin Starkiller]] for the [[Underground Fortress]]. Amber was later the namesake of [[Amber (thumper)|Amber]], a pet [[Thumper (creature)|thumper]] found and adopted by [[Biggs Darklighter/Legends|Biggs]] and [[Windy Starkiller|Windy]], his former charges, on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin]].<ref name="The Star Wars rough draft">[[The Star Wars rough draft]]</ref>

{{Char-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
Amber is perhaps the basis of [[Quarsh Panaka/Legends|Quarsh Panaka]] in [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|Episode I]] as one of the senior bodyguards to the royal family.

